{"title": "Guard cell signal transduction", "url": "https://www.annualreviews.org/doi/abs/10.1146/annurev.arplant.52.1.627", "author": "JI Schroeder and GJ Allen and V Hugouvieux\u2026", "abstract": "\u25aa Abstract Guard cells surround stomatal pores in the epidermis of plant leaves and stems. Stomatal pore opening is essential for CO2 influx into leaves for photosynthetic carbon fixation. In exchange, plants lose over 95% of their water via transpiration to the atmosphere \u2026", "eprint": "https://www.annualreviews.org/doi/full/10.1146/annurev.arplant.52.1.627"}